Which of the following passwords can be used to secure a system such that it will not boot,even if the attacker has physical access to place a USB boot disk in the computer?
A)  GRUB password
B)  UEFI/BIOS password
C)  Root password
D)  SHA1 password
B
B. A password set in the BIOS can be used to prevent the system from booting or handingoff the boot process to a bootloader. Neither GRUB nor a root password will help with thisscenario because physical access is available.
